snippet.textDisplay:
“But if all the scientists and engineers on the planet got together, they’d all be friends.”
Yeah, something about that seems to not work out: the fact that no one can stay truly objective for too long.
I mean, physicists and engineers, definitely. But when we get to social sciences, people will be disagreeing left, right, and centre (especially right and centre, if you know what I mean).
